# Assets

The assets directory contains any assets that need to be referenced within a `.liquid` file, usually using the [asset_url](mdc:https:/shopify.dev/docs/api/liquid/filters/asset_url) Liquid filter.

Assets is a flat directory, it may not contain subdirectories.

Any images that are required in the code, including icons, may be stored within assets.  Icons can be used in `.liquid` files via the [inline_asset_content](mdc:https:/shopify.dev/docs/api/liquid/filters/inline_asset_content) Liquid filter.

## `custom.js` load order

`custom.js` patches `HTMLDialogElement.prototype` for scroll restore and sets `html[scroll-lock]` for dialogs. It must load **before** the user can open cart/quick-add, so in `snippets/scripts.liquid` it is included **immediately after** `dialog.js` with `fetchpriority="high"` (not at the end of the list with `low`).

## `sections/curated-variant-list.liquid`

Homepage-friendly grid of **variant** cards from a **metaobject** entry (not collection metafields). Schema uses `metaobject_type: curated_variant_list` (create that definition in Admin). Loop reads `section.settings.curated_list.product_variants.value`ŌĆöfield handle must match your metaobject list-of-variants field (default dummy handle `product_variants`). Optional **`collection`** setting supplies `closest.collection` for `_product-list-button` (View all) and RTE `closest.collection` in the header.

## Menu drawer layout variables (`custom.js` / `custom.css`)

`syncMenuDrawerLayoutVars` should update **`--menu-drawer-top`** and **`--menu-drawer-height`** on `documentElement`, `body`, and `#Details-menu-drawer-container` only. **`custom.css`** applies `top` / `height` on `#Details-menu-drawer-container[open] > .menu-drawer` via `var(--menu-drawer-top)` and `var(--menu-drawer-height)`. Do **not** set inline `top` / `height` on `.menu-drawer` in JS (harder to override, noisy in DevTools, not Horizon-style). **`--menu-drawer-top` is unset until JS runs** (same in all browsers); CSS `var(--menu-drawer-top, ŌĆ”)` fallbacks apply if missing. **`--menu-drawer-top` does not control the main `#header-component` bar**ŌĆöonly the drawer panel. If **`measureMenuDrawerHeaderBottom()` returns 0** (Safari right after `body: fixed` before header repaints), use **`resolveMenuDrawerHeaderBottomPx`** to fall back to **`--header-group-height` / `--header-height`** from computed style so vars are still sensible.

## Menu drawer: do not unset `.menu-drawer__animated-element` animations

In `custom.css`, avoid `animation: unset !important` (or similar) on `.menu-drawer-container .menu-drawer__animated-element`. HorizonŌĆÖs `header-drawer` uses `onAnimationEnd` on `.menu-drawer` / `.menu-drawer__submenu` after open; nested summaries also rely on `menu-drawer-nav-open` and `animation-fill-mode: backwards` from `snippets/header-drawer.liquid`. Removing those animations causes races when the user opens a nested item (e.g. `#Details-menu-drawer-menu-item-2`) immediately after loadŌĆösubmenus can look like they auto-close or ŌĆ£go back.ŌĆØ To speed the drawer, prefer theme timing tokens (e.g. `--drawer-animation-speed`) or scoped overrides that do not strip submenu/summary animations.

**Submenu summary clicks:** `assets/header-drawer.js` `open()` for `header-drawer/open/submenu` uses `preventDefault()` and programmatic `open` so native `<details>` toggle does not race `requestAnimationFrame` + `menu-open`; a second tap while open calls `#close` instead of relying on the default toggle. While the submenu panel transition runs, `#submenuSlideAnimating` ignores extra summary clicks (double tap / duplicate click); back/close still call `#close` and clear that state. After open animations, if the root drawerŌĆÖs callback runs but a nested `details.menu-drawer__menu-container` is already open, focus is trapped there via `#focusTrapTargetForCompletedOpen`. Stale `onAnimationEnd` open callbacks guard with `details.hasAttribute('open')` before `trapFocus`. Horizontal stagger is overridden in `custom.css` with `@keyframes ssh-menu-drawer-nav-open-ltr` (and `-rtl`) and `animation-name` on `header-drawer .menu-drawer-container[open] .menu-drawer__animated-element` so bundled `menu-drawer-nav-open` (translateY) does not win.

## `html[scroll-lock]` in `custom.css`

Do not add `height` / `max-height` / `100dvh` / `-webkit-fill-available` on `html[scroll-lock]` with dialogs: Horizon applies `body { position:fixed; top:-Ypx }` in the same turn as `showModal()`; heavy html constraints in that frame reset document scroll and the viewport **jumps to the top before the drawer paints**. Keep `overflow: hidden` + `overscroll-behavior` on **html only** ŌĆö do not set `overflow: hidden` on `body` under `html[scroll-lock]` or the sticky `header-component` is clipped and the header **disappears** when the cart drawer opens. `syncDocumentScrollLock()` after `showModal` is deferred one `requestAnimationFrame` for the same reason.

**`<details scroll-lock>` (menu drawer):** `dialog.js` sets `html[scroll-lock]` on `document` **capture** in the same toggle turn. If that runs before `body { position: fixed; top: -Y }`, there is a frame where `html` is `overflow: hidden` but the document still scrollsŌĆö**sticky header can glitch** when opening the drawer on a scrolled page. Mitigation in `custom.js`: (1) a **`window` capture** `toggle` listener (`freezeDetailsBodyBeforeHtmlScrollLock`) applies the body freeze **before** `document` capture; (2) when opening, `syncDocumentScrollLock()` calls `syncDetailsBodyScrollLock()` **before** `setAttribute('scroll-lock')` on `html`. On close, remove `html[scroll-lock]` first, then release the body lock. (3) In that same freeze handler, call **`syncMenuDrawerLayoutVars()`** for the menu drawer so `--menu-drawer-top` / `--menu-drawer-height` are set in the first paint (triple-`rAF` deferral used to let the drawer animate with fallback vars then jump). (4) **`custom.css`**: `transition: none` on `.header[data-sticky-state]` while `html[scroll-lock]:has(#Details-menu-drawer-container[open])` so sticky state flicker does not animate opacity during open. (5) **Safari**: with body fixed, `scrollingElement.scrollTop` can read **0** so header JS sets `data-sticky-state="idle"` (theme uses **opacity:0**) until touch reflows ŌĆö fix with **`syncScrollingElementTopForStickyHeader(y)`** in `custom.js` when applying details body lock, plus **`html[scroll-lock] .header[data-sticky-state='idle'] { opacity: 1 !important; }`** and **`#header-component { transform: translateZ(0) }`** under scroll-lock in `custom.css`.

## `variant-select` (custom.js) and swatches

`onOptionSelect` must call `syncDisplaySwatch(optionEl)` so `.cs-display .swatch-image` matches the selected `.cs-option`; updating only `.cs-display-text` leaves the old image or an empty swatch ring (especially in quick-add after variant change).

## Klaviyo Back in Stock + Horizon

- Put `klaviyo-bis-trigger` only on the **main** PDP add-to-cart (`enable_klaviyo_bis: true` in `add-to-cart-button`, passed from `blocks/add-to-cart.liquid`). Quick-add / cards must **not** use that class or Klaviyo may bind the first match in the DOM to the wrong product.
- Variant updates: `product-form.js` scopes section HTML to `#getFetchedProductFormRoot` and calls `#notifyKlaviyoBisAfterCartButtonMorph` after morphing the cart button.
